sentences: Joey Daleboudt (Dutch: [daləbɑu̯t]; born (1993-07-01)1 July 1993), better known by his stage name Joey Dale, is a Dutch DJ, record producer and musician from Rotterdam.
In 2014, Dale collaborated with Dutch DJ Hardwell to release the song "Arcadia" which charted in Belgium and France.
In 2015, he released "Winds" with Rico & Miella.
In 2016, he collaborated with American producer Ryos to release the song "Armageddon" featuring singer/songwriter Tony Rodini via Revealed Recordings.
2014: Step Into Your Light (featuring Natalie Angiuli) (with Ares Carter)
2016: Where Dreams Are Made (featuring Monstere) [Revealed Recordings]
2017: "Taking Me Home" (with Anthony Dircson featuring Kennedy Ihaka)
2018: "All In My Head" (with Luca Testa featuring Phillip Matta)
